This paper proposes a deep network for image reconstruction and classification problems that involve detection of multiple object instances without any supervision regarding their whereabouts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of auto-encoders and classifiers, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of multi-stage training, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of spatial transformer networks, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM, in that order.
